<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEBushman2005&#91;httpsarchiveorgdetailsjosephsmithrough00bushpage439_439&#93;-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBushman2005[httpsarchiveorgdetailsjosephsmithrough00bushpage439_439]_13-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFBushman2005">Bushman 2005</a>, p.&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/josephsmithrough00bush/page/439">439</a>: "There is no certain evidence that Joseph had sexual relations with any of the wives who were married to other men. They married because Joseph's kingdom grew with the size of his family, and those bonded to that family would be exalted with him."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGoodstein2014" class="citation news cs1">Goodstein, Laurie (10 November 2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/11/us/its-official-mormon-founder-had-up-to-40-wives.html">"It's Official: Mormon Founder Had Up to 40 Wives"</a>. <i>The New York Times</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2 June</span> 2017</span>. <q>[Joseph Smith Jr.] married Helen Mar Kimball, a daughter of two close friends, 'several months before her 15th birthday'.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=It%27s+Official%3A+Mormon+Founder+Had+Up+to+40+Wives&amp;rft.date=2014-11-10&amp;rft.aulast=Goodstein&amp;rft.aufirst=Laurie&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2014%2F11%2F11%2Fus%2Fits-official-mormon-founder-had-up-to-40-wives.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTurner2012" class="citation news cs1">Turner, John G. (27 October 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/john-g-turner/brigham-young-and-polygamy_b_1792555.html">"Polygamy, Brigham Young and His 55 Wives"</a>. <i>The Huffington Post</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2 June</span> 2017</span>. <q>The sheer variety of Brigham Young's marriages makes it difficult to make sense of them. He married — was sealed to, in Mormon parlance — young (Clarissa Decker, 15) and old (Hannah Tapfield King, 65).</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Huffington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=Polygamy%2C+Brigham+Young+and+His+55+Wives&amp;rft.date=2012-10-27&amp;rft.aulast=Turner&amp;rft.aufirst=John+G.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2Fjohn-g-turner%2Fbrigham-young-and-polygamy_b_1792555.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
