<li id="cite_note-208"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-208">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGalliherBradshawHydeDehlin2015" class="citation journal cs1">Galliher, Renee; Bradshaw, William; Hyde, Daniel; Dehlin, John; Crowell, Katherine (April 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/260873307">"Sexual orientation change efforts among current or former LDS church members"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Counseling_Psychology" title="Journal of Counseling Psychology">Journal of Counseling Psychology</a></i>. <b>62</b> (2): 95–105. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1037%2Fcou0000011">10.1037/cou0000011</a>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24635593">24635593</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/ResearchGate" title="ResearchGate">ResearchGate</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Counseling+Psychology&amp;rft.atitle=Sexual+orientation+change+efforts+among+current+or+former+LDS+church+members&amp;rft.volume=62&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=95-105&amp;rft.date=2015-04&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1037%2Fcou0000011&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F24635593&amp;rft.aulast=Galliher&amp;rft.aufirst=Renee&amp;rft.au=Bradshaw%2C+William&amp;rft.au=Hyde%2C+Daniel&amp;rft.au=Dehlin%2C+John&amp;rft.au=Crowell%2C+Katherine&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F260873307&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-209"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-209">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFishRussell2020" class="citation journal cs1">Fish, Jessica N.; Russell, Stephen T. (Aug 2020). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7349462">"Sexual Orientation and Gender Identity Change Efforts are Unethical and Harmful"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/American_Journal_of_Public_Health" title="American Journal of Public Health">American Journal of Public Health</a></i>. <b>110</b> (8): 1113–1114. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2105%2FAJPH.2020.305765">10.2105/AJPH.2020.305765</a>. <a href="/wiki/PMC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMC (identifier)">PMC</a>&#160;<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7349462">7349462</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32639919">32639919</a>. <q>With substantial evidence of serious harms associated with exposure to [sexual orientation and gender identity change efforts (SOGICE)] particularly for minors, 21 states (and multiple cities and counties) have passed bipartisan laws or regulations prohibiting SOGICE. ... Furthermore, compared with LGBTQ youths with no exposure, those exposed to SOGICE showed 1.76 times greater odds of seriously considering suicide, 2.23 times greater odds of having attempted suicide, and 2.54 times greater odds of multiple suicide attempts in the previous year.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Journal+of+Public+Health&amp;rft.atitle=Sexual+Orientation+and+Gender+Identity+Change+Efforts+are+Unethical+and+Harmful&amp;rft.volume=110&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.pages=1113-1114&amp;rft.date=2020-08&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7349462%23id-name%3DPMC&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F32639919&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2105%2FAJPH.2020.305765&amp;rft.aulast=Fish&amp;rft.aufirst=Jessica+N.&amp;rft.au=Russell%2C+Stephen+T.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7349462&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-210"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-210">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPhillips2005" class="citation book cs1">Phillips, Rick (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/269701629"><i>Conservative Christian Identity &amp; Same-Sex Orientation: The Case of Gay Mormons</i></a>. Frankfurt, Germany: <a href="/wiki/Peter_Lang_Publishing" class="mw-redirect" title="Peter Lang Publishing">Peter Lang Publishing</a>. p.&#160;11. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0820474809" title="Special:BookSources/978-0820474809"><bdi>978-0820474809</bdi></a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170418092803/https://www.uvu.edu/religiousstudies/docs/msc_philips_conservative.pdf">Archived</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> from the original on April 18, 2017<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">31 May</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Conservative+Christian+Identity+%26+Same-Sex+Orientation%3A+The+Case+of+Gay+Mormons&amp;rft.place=Frankfurt%2C+Germany&amp;rft.pages=11&amp;rft.pub=Peter+Lang+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=978-0820474809&amp;rft.aulast=Phillips&amp;rft.aufirst=Rick&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F269701629&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-211"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-211">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCook2017" class="citation journal cs1">Cook, Bryce (Summer 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.50.2.0001">"What Do We Know of God's Will for His LGBT Children? An Examination of the LDS Church's Current Position on Homosexuality"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>50</b> (2): 20–21. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.50.2.0001">10.5406/dialjmormthou.50.2.0001</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:190443414">190443414</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=What+Do+We+Know+of+God%27s+Will+for+His+LGBT+Children%3F+An+Examination+of+the+LDS+Church%27s+Current+Position+on+Homosexuality&amp;rft.ssn=summer&amp;rft.volume=50&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=20-21&amp;rft.date=2017&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.50.2.0001&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A190443414%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft.aulast=Cook&amp;rft.aufirst=Bryce&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.5406%252Fdialjmormthou.50.2.0001&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-212"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-212">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGalliherBradshawDehlinCrowelle2014" class="citation journal cs1">Galliher, Renee; Bradshaw, William; Dehlin, John; Crowelle, Katherine (25 April 2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/273248065">"Psychosocial Correlates of Religious Approaches to Same-Sex Attraction: A Mormon Perspective"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Gay_%26_Lesbian_Mental_Health" title="Journal of Gay &amp; Lesbian Mental Health">Journal of Gay &amp; Lesbian Mental Health</a></i>. <b>18</b> (3): 301, 304. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1080%2F19359705.2014.912970">10.1080/19359705.2014.912970</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:144153586">144153586</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/ResearchGate" title="ResearchGate">ResearchGate</a>. <q>The major findings from the study are that non-biologically based views regarding the etiology of SSA [same-sex attraction], remaining active in the LDS Church, remaining single, and engaging in mixed-orientation marriages were all associated with higher reported levels of internalized homophobia, sexual identity distress, and depression, and lower levels of self-esteem and quality of life. ... This study does affirm and extend the existing literature by suggesting that psychosocially based beliefs about SSA etiology active participation in non-LGBT-affirming churches, being single and celibate, and mixed-orientation marriage—all of which are common beliefs and/or practices within modern, active LDS culture—are associated with poorer psychosocial health, well-being, and quality of life for LGBT Mormons. Conversely, biological beliefs about SSA etiology, complete disaffiliation from the LDS Church, legal same-sex marriage, and sexual activity are all associated with higher levels of psychosocial health, well-being, and quality of life for LGBT Mormons.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Gay+%26+Lesbian+Mental+Health&amp;rft.atitle=Psychosocial+Correlates+of+Religious+Approaches+to+Same-Sex+Attraction%3A+A+Mormon+Perspective&amp;rft.volume=18&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=301%2C+304&amp;rft.date=2014-04-25&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1080%2F19359705.2014.912970&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A144153586%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft.aulast=Galliher&amp;rft.aufirst=Renee&amp;rft.au=Bradshaw%2C+William&amp;rft.au=Dehlin%2C+John&amp;rft.au=Crowelle%2C+Katherine&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F273248065&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-213"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-213">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSimmons2017" class="citation journal cs1">Simmons, Brian (December 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://getd.libs.uga.edu/pdfs/simmons_brian_w_201712_phd.pdf">"Coming out Mormon: An examination of religious orientation, spiritual trauma, and PTSD among Mormon and ex-Mormon LGBTQQA adults"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>University of Georgia Theses and Dissertations</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Georgia" title="University of Georgia">University of Georgia</a>: 99.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=University+of+Georgia+Theses+and+Dissertations&amp;rft.atitle=Coming+out+Mormon%3A+An+examination+of+religious+orientation%2C+spiritual+trauma%2C+and+PTSD+among+Mormon+and+ex-Mormon+LGBTQQA+adults&amp;rft.pages=99&amp;rft.date=2017-12&amp;rft.aulast=Simmons&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgetd.libs.uga.edu%2Fpdfs%2Fsimmons_brian_w_201712_phd.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-214"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-214">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilliams2017" class="citation journal cs1">Williams, Brian (December 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://athenaeum.libs.uga.edu/handle/10724/38227">"Coming out Mormon"</a>. <i>uga.edu</i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Georgia" title="University of Georgia">University of Georgia</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=uga.edu&amp;rft.atitle=Coming+out+Mormon&amp;rft.date=2017-12&amp;rft.aulast=Williams&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fathenaeum.libs.uga.edu%2Fhandle%2F10724%2F38227&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACriticism+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
